      • checkRefID

        public void checkRefID(Run object)
        A method to be called before the marshall process. Whenever a referenced object is set, its refID should be updated automatically, so that the refID and the ID of the object are always in sync. Here we check that this is the case.
        Specified by:
        checkRefID in class AbstractReferenceResolver<Run>
        Parameters:
        object - The Object to check for reference ID integrity.
